We recently tried to export data from a mysql 3.0.2 confluence instance using the atlassia site backups feature and then import that data into a MSSQL confluence instance .. it had issues which has meant we have had to investigate using mysql 'sqlserver "compatible" dumps' as an alternative.

IMO the atlassian xml backup dumps should abstract themselves to data types which are DB independant, the individual confluence install should be able to interpret the xml backup and recreate the data no matter what database is being used.

I have set the priority as 'major' since we have yet to execute a succesful solution to this problem, when/if our current experiments fail I will be requesting escalation of this issue to critical/blocker.

