RSS feeds generated with FeedBuilder always include the *unrendered* page content (that is, the wiki markup), rather than rendering it into HTML.  This may be fine for "internal" consumption, but it makes it less useful for a public-facing RSS feed.  For example, I don't want our users to see this:

{code}
  Visit our [support site|http://www.example.org/some/ridiculous/path?with=parameters&other=things].
{code}

I want them to see this:

  Visit our support site.

And I want them to be able to click on the link.

Because I can see an argument for supporting both models (rendered and unrendered content), I'm proposing that this should be configureable via some sort of checkbox.

