For PDF export it is possible to define the layout and style for the exported pdf.

However, in order to test the layout you need to export the entire pdf and if something goes wrong you need to check out the html export generated in the temp directory. 

Its not particularly user friendly, so it would be really useful if there was a way to preview the html/css generation without having to go through PDF generation.

OSGi bundles, which are handled as regular Atlassian plugins, cannot be upgraded due to an exception that looks something like this:
{noformat}
java.io.FileNotFoundException: /home/mrdon/dev/autoexport-plugin/target/confluence/home/plugins-osgi-cache/felix/bundle18/bundle.state (No such file or directory){noformat}

What is happening is the version of Atlassian Plugins that ships with 3.0.1 and 3.0.2 (2.2.3.rc1) has a bug that tries to stop an uninstalled plugin, which fails.  This was fixed in https://studio.atlassian.com/browse/PLUG-409 but unreleased, so Confluence will need a release of Plugins 2.2.5.

